---
import UseCase from '../../../UseCase.astro';
import UseCaseInteractive from '../../../UseCaseInteractive.astro';
import Usage from '../../../Usage.astro';
import UsageItem from '../../../UsageItem.astro';
---

<UseCase
  title="Clarify Uncertainty and Limitations Explicitly"
  description="Be explicit about what the AI doesn't know, what it can't do, and what factors might affect the accuracy of its outputs."
>
  <UseCaseInteractive clsHeight={112} label="Explicit limitations" toggle>
    <div class="grid gap-600 w-full">
      <div class="grid gap-400 p-600 rounded-lg bg-tone-neutral-09 border border-tone-neutral-03">
        <div class="grid gap-200">
          <mds-text typography="label"><b>Translation with Limitations</b></mds-text>
          <mds-text typography="body">Translation: "Hello, how are you?"</mds-text>
          <div class="p-400 rounded bg-status-info-10 border border-status-info-03">
            <mds-text typography="caption"
              ><b>Limitations:</b> This translation is based on common usage. It may not capture regional
              dialects, slang, or context-specific meanings. For formal or legal documents, please consult
              a professional translator.</mds-text
            >
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div
        class="grid gap-400 p-600 rounded-lg bg-status-warning-10 border border-status-warning-03"
      >
        <div class="grid gap-200">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-200">
            <mds-icon name="mi/outline/warning-amber" class="text-status-warning-05"></mds-icon>
            <mds-text typography="label"><b>Low Confidence Output</b></mds-text>
          </div>
          <mds-text typography="body"
            >This document appears to be a contract (45% confidence).</mds-text
          >
          <mds-text typography="caption" class="text-status-warning-06"
            ><b>Why uncertain:</b> The document contains mixed language patterns. It might be a contract,
            legal brief, or formal agreement. I don't have enough examples of this specific document type
            in my training data.</mds-text
          >
          <mds-text typography="caption" class="text-status-warning-06"
            ><b>What I can't do:</b> I cannot determine legal validity, identify missing clauses, or assess
            compliance requirements.</mds-text
          >
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="grid gap-400 p-600 rounded-lg bg-status-error-10 border border-status-error-03">
        <div class="grid gap-200">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-200">
            <mds-icon name="mi/outline/error" class="text-status-error-05"></mds-icon>
            <mds-text typography="label"><b>No Limitations Mentioned (Problematic)</b></mds-text>
          </div>
          <mds-text typography="body">Translation: "Hello, how are you?"</mds-text>
          <mds-text typography="caption" class="text-status-error-06"
            >This presents the translation without mentioning limitations, leading users to assume
            it's always accurate and appropriate for all contexts.</mds-text
          >
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </UseCaseInteractive>
  <Usage>
    <UsageItem variant="do">
      Explicitly state what the AI doesn't know or can't determine.
    </UsageItem>
    <UsageItem variant="dont">
      Present outputs without mentioning limitations or uncertainty.
    </UsageItem>
    <UsageItem variant="do">
      Explain what factors might affect accuracy or when the output might not be reliable.
    </UsageItem>
    <UsageItem variant="dont">
      Let users discover limitations only after they've relied on incorrect outputs.
    </UsageItem>
  </Usage>
</UseCase>
